abstract: Rent regulations, climate change, gun control and more: Lawmakers pushed through an undeniably liberal agenda.
snippet: Rent regulations, climate change, gun control and more: Lawmakers pushed through an undeniably liberal agenda.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY — At 7:20 a.m., after an all-night marathon marked by the passage of dozens of bills and a rubber-band fight on the floor of the chamber, the Legislature on Friday finally ended a 2019 session that was nothing short of groundbreaking.

abstract: The New England Patriots owner, who has been under legal scrutiny in a Florida prostitution case, accepted one of Israel’s most prestigious awards for his philanthropy there.
snippet: The New England Patriots owner, who has been under legal scrutiny in a Florida prostitution case, accepted one of Israel’s most prestigious awards for his philanthropy there.
lead_paragraph: After New England Patriots owner Robert K. Kraft was charged in February with soliciting prostitution, some of the many charities that he has supported wrestled with what to do.

lead_paragraph: Andrea Colon, an 18-year-old student activist from Far Rockaway, Queens, traveled a thousand miles to a presidential campaign stop for Mayor Bill de Blasio in Hiawatha, Iowa — not to hear his views on national issues, but to confront him about arrests in schools.

abstract: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
snippet: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
lead_paragraph: Julius Alan Schorzman and Louis Edward Morton met as teammates while playing for the Seattle Quake Rugby Football Club, an L.G.B.T.-inclusive rugby club, in May 2017. Mr. Schorzman had joined the team when Mr. Morton was away on a six-month airline assignment in Chicago.
